```plantuml
@startuml aws-solutions_automated-security-response-on-aws
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor User

rectangle "AWS Security Hub" as SecurityHub #lightyellow

rectangle "EventBridge" as EventBridge #lightblue

rectangle "Orchestrator\n(Step Function)" as Orchestrator #lightgreen

rectangle "SSM Automation\nDocuments" as SSMAutomation #lightcoral

rectangle "Custom Actions" as CustomActions #lightgrey

rectangle "Lambda Functions" as LambdaFunctions #lightpink

rectangle "CloudWatch" as CloudWatch #aliceblue

rectangle "SQS" as SQS #beige

rectangle "External Ticketing\nSystems (Jira, ServiceNow)" as Ticketing #lightsteelblue

' ========== Connections ==========
User --> SecurityHub : View findings\nTrigger custom actions

' Security Hub interactions
SecurityHub --> EventBridge : Send findings
EventBridge --> Orchestrator : Trigger remediation workflow

' Orchestrator interactions
Orchestrator --> SSMAutomation : Initiate SSM documents
Orchestrator --> LambdaFunctions : Execute remediation logic

' Lambda Functions interactions
LambdaFunctions --> SecurityHub : Update finding status
LambdaFunctions --> CloudWatch : Log metrics and outcomes
LambdaFunctions --> SQS : Queue remediation tasks
LambdaFunctions --> Ticketing : Create tickets post-remediation

' Custom Actions interactions
CustomActions --> EventBridge : Trigger via custom action

' CloudWatch interactions
CloudWatch --> User : Monitor metrics and alerts

@enduml
```